    <!-- Tab 1: Role Overview -->
    <div id="overview" class="tab-content active">
        <h2>What is a Steno Tech Assistant (STA)?</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin: 20px 0;">A Steno Tech Assistant provides technical support for depositions where video recording is not the primary focus. Your role centers on ensuring smooth technical operation, participant assistance, and supporting the Court Reporter.</p>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <strong>When You'll Be Assigned as an STA:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>A video product is <strong>NOT</strong> ordered (client receives transcript only)</li>
                <li>The job is on <strong>Zoom with the Steno Connect App</strong> AND the attorney hasn't completed a Demo OR has requested assistance</li>
                <li>The job has an <strong>REA service</strong> (Remote Exhibit Assistant)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <h3 style="margin-top: 30px; color: #2F4A56;">Your Core Responsibilities</h3>
        <div class="accordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    üõ†Ô∏è Technical Support
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-content">
                    <p>Address any technical issues as participants join the room. Ensure everyone can hear and see clearly.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    üë• Participant Assistance
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-content">
                    <p>Distribute guest mode invites to all participants and guide them on using the Steno Connect App for Zoom (ZCONN) and its features.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    üìé Exhibit Handling
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-content">
                    <p>Instruct the Taking Attorney on uploading exhibits to the ZCONN app, provide general recommendations, and pass the deposition over to the CR to initiate proceedings.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    üëÄ Observation Period
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-content">
                    <p>Remain in the deposition for <strong>15 minutes</strong> after the CR begins to monitor for any technical issues.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header" onclick="toggleAccordion(this)">
                    üö™ Transitioning Host Role
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-content">
                    <p>If no issues arise after 15 minutes, designate the CR as the host and exit the room. Provide the tech line number: <strong>888.404.0390</strong></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Tab 2: Key Differences -->
    <div id="differences" class="tab-content">
        <h2>Key Differences: STA vs Videographer</h2>
        
        <div class="comparison">
            <div class="comparison-card">
                <div class="icon">üé•</div>
                <h3>Videographer</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Creates video recording product</li>
                    <li>Uses AWS/OBS for backup</li>
                    <li>Reads official read-on</li>
                    <li>Stays entire deposition</li>
                    <li>Manages START/STOP workflow</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="comparison-card">
                <div class="icon">üìã</div>
                <h3>STA (You!)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Provides tech support only</li>
                    <li>No AWS/OBS backup needed</li>
                    <li>NO official read-on</li>
                    <li>Exits after 15 minutes</li>
                    <li>No START/STOP workflow</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="alert">
            <div>
                <strong>CRITICAL: Recording Management</strong><br>
                <strong>If Zoom recording was ON when you joined:</strong> DO NOT turn it off<br>
                <strong>If Zoom recording was OFF when you joined:</strong> DO NOT turn it on<br>
                The recording is for the Court Reporter's audio, NOT for video production.
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-box">
            <strong>Timing & Duration:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Join <strong>30 minutes before start time</strong> (same as videographer)</li>
                <li>Sessions typically last <strong>45 minutes</strong></li>
                <li>You'll exit after <strong>15-minute observation period</strong> (if no issues)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-box" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <strong>What You WILL Do:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>‚úì Read General Recommendations (off the record)</li>
                <li>‚úì Greet participants and provide tech support</li>
                <li>‚úì Guide participants through SC App</li>
                <li>‚úì Monitor for 15 minutes after CR begins</li>
            </ul>
            
            <strong style="display: block; margin-top: 15px;">What You WON'T Do:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>‚úó Official read-on (CR handles this)</li>
                <li>‚úó AWS/OBS backup recording</li>
                <li>‚úó Video production or editing</li>
                <li>‚úó Stay for entire deposition</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="info-box" style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <strong>Zoom Setup Reminders:</strong>
            <ul style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <li>Rename yourself: <strong>"Your Name (Steno Tech Assistant)"</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Unless absolutely necessary, do NOT claim Zoom host</strong></li>
                <li>If needed, use host key: <strong>012219</strong></li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
